Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of information and communication technology (ICT) in improving traffic signal control, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of autonomous and self-organized traffic signaling control, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the need for real-time sensing of traffic patterns and a priori knowledge of traffic flow, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for communication between traffic signals to improve overall traffic efficiency, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
